Current State (MPT/v05.24)
Protocol Architecture:

Pure SPV Protocol Layer (tokenProtocol.ts): Zero network dependencies; validates tokens via Merkle proofs + block headers
Token ID: SHA-256(genesisTxId || outputIndex LE || immutableChunkBytes) — cryptographically binds identity to immutable metadata
Two Token Modes:
NFT: Each 1-sat output = unique token (fragments via divisibility)
Fungible: All UTXOs share 1 Token ID, satoshis = token units
Core Features (v05.24 latest):

Genesis transactions mint tokens with OP_RETURN metadata
Transfer transactions carry proof chains (Merkle proof history)
SPV verification gate: Token ID check → Merkle proof verification → Block header confirmation
UTXO Quarantine: 1-sat outputs protected from accidental spending
File embedding: SHA-256 hash in tokenAttributes, full file in separate OP_RETURN
Fragment tracking: Divisible tokens grouped by NFT number with completion tracking
Auto-confirmation polling for transfer status
Code Organization:

tokenProtocol.ts — Cryptography (computeTokenId, Merkle proof verification)
opReturnCodec.ts — OP_RETURN encoding/decoding with proof chain binary format
tokenBuilder.ts — Token lifecycle (mint, transfer, verify, import)
walletProvider.ts — Network layer (WhatsOnChain API)
tokenStore.ts — localStorage persistence (tokens + proof chains)
app.ts — Browser UI with minting, transfer, verification interfaces
Refactoring Scope: MPT → P Token Protocol
What Stays the Same:

Core cryptographic verification logic (SHA-256, Merkle proofs, block headers)
Token lifecycle and transaction structure
Both NFT and Fungible modes
Proof chain architecture
What Changes (Naming/Branding):

Protocol Identifier: "MPT" (0x4d 0x50 0x54) → "P" or "PTP" (new prefix bytes)
Version Byte: 0x02 → TBD (consider 0x01 for P protocol v1 or 0x02 for continuity)
File Marker: "MPT-FILE" → "P-FILE" or similar
Constant Names: MPT_PREFIX, MPT_VERSION, MPT_FILE_MARKER → P-equivalents
Documentation: All references to "Merkle Proof Token" → new protocol name
Impact Areas:

OP_RETURN parsing/encoding (version detection, chunk layout)
Block explorers and external indexing (old MPT tokens remain on-chain; P tokens are new)
Wallet UI labels and documentation
localStorage keys (could namespace by protocol: p:data:token vs mpt:data:token)
